

	 
       Counting Sheep  Lying there Peaceful in bed Praying that the fear inside Is only in your head Keep counting sheep, little one Dont shut your precious eyes Keep counting sheep, my little one Or say you sweet goodbyes The voice so far away And those glowing yellow eyes Staying under your covers Is what anyone would advise But there, lurking in the shadows Something far, yet way too near Living in your nightmares And feeding off your fear Waiting for the second You let your guard down And close your eyes to go to sleep So it can prance right off the ground Dont go to sleep, little child For when you do, he will be there Dont go to sleep, little child For no fear will ever compare Hes waiting for the moment That your eyes begin to close So dont go to sleep, little child For where he is, nobody knows
     
    
